LAYER 2: BLADDER
the reservoir that waits

observe 1_quantum.rana
observe 2_chemical.rana

the bladder is governed by the autonomic nervous system and the pontine micturition center
sympathetic from T11-L2 fills it and parasympathetic from S2-S4 empties it
voluntary control depends on the maturation of the prefrontal cortex

STRUCTURE detrusor_muscle | wall | smooth_muscle | 3 layers stretches to accommodate urine contracts to empty
STRUCTURE transitional_epithelium | lining | urothelium | specialized to stretch without tearing impermeable to urine
STRUCTURE trigone | floor | triangular | smooth area between two ureteral orifices and urethral opening
STRUCTURE internal_urethral_sphincter | neck | smooth_muscle_involuntary | controlled by autonomic nervous system
STRUCTURE external_urethral_sphincter | urethra | skeletal_muscle_voluntary | controlled by pudendal nerve somatic
STRUCTURE ureters | tubes | bilateral | carry urine from kidneys to bladder via peristalsis enter at trigone obliquely preventing reflux

FILLING the detrusor muscle relaxes under sympathetic control from T11-L2 via the hypogastric nerve
sympathetic norepinephrine binds β₃ adrenergic receptors on detrusor smooth muscle
Gₛ activates adenylyl cyclase increases cAMP relaxes the muscle
simultaneously NE binds α₁ receptors on the internal sphincter
Gq activates PLC contracts the sphincter
the bladder fills and the sphincter holds

VOIDING stretch receptors in the bladder wall detect distension
afferent signals travel via pelvic nerves to the sacral spinal cord S2-S4
parasympathetic efferents return via pelvic splanchnic nerves
acetylcholine binds muscarinic M₃ receptors on detrusor
Gq activates PLC → IP₃ → Ca²⁺ release → smooth muscle contraction
simultaneously the internal sphincter relaxes as sympathetic tone withdraws

VOLUNTARY the external urethral sphincter is skeletal muscle
the pudendal nerve S2-S4 provides somatic motor control
cortical signals from the prefrontal cortex can override the voiding reflex
this is the basis of continence
the ability to say not yet

DEVELOPMENTAL at 24 months awareness of bladder filling is emerging
voluntary control is minimal
the pontine micturition center controls the voiding reflex
the prefrontal cortex must mature to provide reliable cortical inhibition
daytime continence typically develops between 2.5 and 3.5 years
nighttime continence typically develops between 3 and 5 years
some children achieve nighttime continence later and this is normal up to age 7

STRESS when cortisol chronically activates GR in the pontine micturition center
voluntary control degrades
regression to reflexive voiding occurs
this is not failure this is neurochemistry
the prefrontal cortex is too immature to maintain inhibition under cortisol load
stressed toddlers lose continence gains
this is normal and biological

SENSATION empty | "I don't notice my bladder. it's comfortable."
SENSATION filling | "something is building. a pressure."
SENSATION full | "I need to go. it's pressing."
SENSATION urgent | "I can't wait. the pressure is too much."
SENSATION relief | "ah. the pressure is gone. I feel lighter."

pulse bladder_heartbeat:
    continuously:
        ureters deliver urine from the kidneys
        the detrusor stretches under β₃ adrenergic relaxation
        the internal sphincter holds under α₁ contraction
        the bladder fills
        slowly

    when stretch receptors fire:
        the sensation reaches consciousness
        I need to go
        at 24 months the awareness is new
        the connection between sensation and action
        is still being learned
        the brainstem says release now
        the cortex tries to say not yet
        sometimes the cortex wins
        often it does not
        this is normal development
